Driving in high heels is dangerous!
Accidents involving incorrect pedaling of young people - Yahoo!
Violations in violation of the Road Traffic Act
The number of reports on accidents caused by incorrect operation such as pedal treading has been increasing, and it is a big mistake to think that this is a problem only for elderly drivers.
According to the 2015 National Police Agency data, more than 1080 pedal misstep accidents occurred at the age of 24 and over 1032.
It is important to call attention to young people as well.
do you want to take your feet?
is it safe?
There is no description of the gender ratio or cause of this data, but unlike elderly people who are often thought to come from a decline in their bodies, such as driving skills and reflexes, in the younger generation, it is possible to mistake inadvertently due to other things such as music and conversation, and trampling due to clothes etc.
In particular, women choose various shoes depending on their day's clothing, such as high heels, pumps, sandals, and mules, and some drive as they are.
Although some people know that it is not suitable for driving, it is troublesome to change shoes, some people do not think about the possibility that it will lead to danger at all, and many people drive without evil.
However, driving in high heels and sandals violates the Road Traffic Act.
The first is "Reliable operation of steering wheel, brake and other operations" Article 70 "Contrary to safety driving obligations" which stipulates that "Do not drive in such a way that causes accidents and harms people."
The other is Article 71, which stipulates that drivers must comply with the matters stipulated by each prefectural public safety committee, for example, in Article 12 of the Miyazaki Prefectural Road Traffic Law Enforcement Regulations, for example, "Do not drive vehicles (except light vehicles) by wearing shoes in a manner that prevents driving operations, or by wearing shoes that may interfere with driving operations."
Even if it is not specified as a high heel, the purpose of each prefecture is similar to that of regard as a violation of driving in " footwear that may interfere with driving operation."
So why is driving at high heels dangerous?
It is obvious considering the basics of safely pedaling.
For safe pedal operation, first fix the heel of the foot on the floor, place the foot to be perpendicular to the brake pedal, and when stepping on the accelerator pedal, tilt the foot to the right as a starting point.
At this time, regardless of the behavior of the car, it is important to keep firmly fixed so that the heel does not break.
However, in high heels, the area where the heels are grounded on the floor is small, and the heels always blur and blur.
This may lead to danger.
In addition, most cars have floor carpets, but this material is easy to catch a high heel or heel, and sometimes when the heel is caught and the pedal cannot be stepped in, or when the heel is pulled, the high heel can be removed and stuck in the back of the pedal.
In addition, there is a case where the heel pulls to the back of the pedal when stepping back after stepping on the pedal, and the accelerator pedal disappears.
Toyota and Subaru Accelerate Joint Development (Response) - Yahoo!News
Toyota and Subaru agreed on a new business capital alliance on September 27.
Toyota will acquire additional Subaru shares and become an affiliate of equity method application.
Since the partnership agreement was reached in 2005, the two companies have been working together to produce Toyota vehicles, supply Toyota vehicles to Subaru, and jointly develop the FR sports car 86.
In June this year, we also agreed to develop EV-specific platforms and EV vehicles using Subaru's All-wheel drive technology and Toyota's electrification technology.
In this agreement, Toyota will acquire additional Subaru shares.
At present, Toyota's shareholding in Subaru is 16.83 percent of the voting rights.
The company is a subsidiary of Toyota.
On the other hand, Subaru will acquire Toyota shares which are equivalent to the same amount (up to 80 billion yen) as the amount required for the acquisition of Subaru shares.
Both companies develop and strengthen cooperation through business capital alliances.
We will jointly develop AWD and 86/BRZ models, expand the installation of THS (Toyota Hybrid System) in Subaru vehicles, coordinate in the connected area, and promote technological collaboration in the autonomous driving field.
U.S., at least 18,000 refugees | Shizuoka Shimbun
Washington, D.C. On October 26, the U.S. Department of State announced a policy to reduce the number of refugees accepted from all over the world to 18,000 in the fiscal year ending October 19-20.
The minimum number of refugees since 1980 has been renewed for three consecutive years.
The Trump administration is aiming to appeal strict immigration and refugee policies to the conservatives in the presidential election next year.
It is inevitable that criticism from human rights groups and other organizations will be made in the midst of people being driven out of the country in various places.
The previous Obama administration set the maximum limit for fiscal 2017 to 110,000, but the Trump administration, which was inaugurated in January 2017, reversed it and reduced it to 50,000.
In fiscal 2018, the number of employees decreased to 45,000 and in fiscal 2007 to 30,000.
