<Saga Torrential Rainfall and Support Wheel< Specialty Noodles "Taromen" Perform at evacuation centers Operation Co-op to cheer up victims|Saga Newspaper News|Saga Newspapers
Children who enjoy the soul food "Taromen" in Omachi on the way home from the bath = Misato, Omachi Town General Welfare Center
"Omachi Taromen Steering Council" (Representative of Kensuke Suzuyama) made at a restaurant serving "Taromen," a specialty noodle of Omachi-cho, performed "Taromen" at Misato, Machi General Welfare Center, which is a shelter for people affected by heavy rain on the night of the 25th.
The soul food that was loved since the Kishima coal mine was there cheered the people affected.
"The only thing we can do is make noodles and eat them."
Four restaurants on the taromen menu cooperated to make 90 meals and brought rice balls to shelter.
Udon noodles of fine noodles were put in ginger-flavored beef bone soup and plenty of ingredients such as pork head meat, shrimp and vegetables were served.
Not only the people living in evacuation centers but also those who came to the baths provided "taste of Omachi."
A man (66) says, "I've been a fan since I was young, but I ate it for the first time in a year," and a 20-year-old and 22-year-old siblings who moved about a year ago and said, "I ate it for the first time, it's delicious, I want to go to the store this time."
Deputy representative Kenichiro Fujise, who finished cooking, ran up and said, "We will cooperate if we can do anything so that we can return to our daily life as soon as possible."
1 year after the earthquake in the eastern part of Iburi Province: Water is secured even during power outages.
In response to the total blackout caused by the Iburi Eastern Earthquake in September last year, measures are being taken at condominiums in Hakodate City, where severe flooding occurred.
According to the Water and Sewer Department of the City Bureau of Enterprises, seven condominiums were installed in one year after the earthquake, and "watering plugs" were installed to allow water to be discharged even if power outages occurred.
There are about 400 condominiums and private housing units in the city that are more than four stories above the water supply by the "passenger tank type" that can be cut off when power outages occur, and the department calls for consideration of countermeasures.
The water supply system for houses is broadly divided into two types: the "passenger tank type" that once feeds water into a receiving tank located underground or on the roof, and the "directly connected type" that directly feeds water from the city's water distribution pipe to each door.
Even if the water pipe is not damaged, electric pumps that pump water from the water tank to each door will not be able to run due to power failure, and each door will be cut off.
Training (Aomori Broadcasting Corporation) - Yahoo!
A training session was held in Shingo Village to search and rescue people who had lost their lives before the autumn mushroom harvesting season.
60 people from the police, the fire department and the hunting party participated in the training held at Hirakozawa Forest Park in Shingo Village.
At the opening ceremony, Chief Tsukeda of the Goto Police Department called for close cooperation and training.
★ Takahashi Regional Manager's declaration "We will start mountain training rescue training from this."
The training was conducted on the assumption that a man who went out to see the mushroom harvest would not return home even at night.
The participants are divided into three groups and search the mountain by calling the name of the missing man.
In Shingo Village, a 70-year-old man who entered the mountain to pick wild vegetables in June disappeared and was rescued the next day with injuries.
During the training, I found a man who had been injured and checked the cooperation from the search to rescue him on a stretcher.
