New charges for mobile phones Price reduction in fair competition: Hokkaido Shimbun
A new fee plan for a mobile phone company was released in response to the revision of the Telecommunications Business Act in October.
However, it was generally high.
Chief Cabinet Secretary Yoshihide Suga said last summer, "There is room to lower the price by about 40 percent," and despite high expectations for price reduction, there was no price competition.
Rakuten's full-scale entry into the market was postponed, and the oligopoly state of the three major companies continued.
It is desirable for consumers to have a fee system that is easy to use by fair competition.
I want to ask for the efforts of the mobile companies.
The amended Act prohibits set discounts on terminal charges and communications charges.
Instead of cheaply selling the terminal fee, the communication fee was set to increase.
SoftBank and KDDI (au) announced plans to increase the number of devices to half.
However, both companies have a "SIM Lock" that cannot be used by other companies for 100 days.
NTT Docomo will charge up to one third of the terminal fee only for subscribers of its own line.
It seems that the three companies continue to "enclosure" to prevent transfers to other companies.
The Ministry of Internal Affairs and Communications (MIC) announced that it would require immediate termination of SIM locks.
Companies must respond promptly.
Rakuten's postponement was due to the lack of communication networks such as base stations.
It was expected to be an explosive in the price reduction competition, so it looked like a shoulder strap.
Is there a sweetness of the outlook?
The timing and prices of full-scale services have not been disclosed.
As a company responsible for social infrastructure, I would like you to take responsibility for your business.
The price revision was triggered by the remarks of Chief Cabinet Secretary Suga.
Mr. Suga expressed his dissatisfaction with the new charges of the three companies, saying, "I think competition will start from now on, and I do not think that it will be fine."
However, the government-made price reduction does not seem to distort the market and encourage sound competition.
Companies should develop customer-oriented competition before they are told by the government.
Each company's fee system is very complex and difficult to compare.
The Consumer Affairs Agency called for attention as there were cases where the consumer's burden exceeded the half price even though the terminal advertises such as "maximum half price."
Companies should make careful and easy-to-understand explanations so as not to mislead users themselves.
Cash card of 3 Shinkin in Mie Prefecture - Ise Shimbun
Three Shinkin Banks in Mie Prefecture (Kuwana Mie Shinkin Bank, Kita-Ise Ueno Shinkin Bank, and Kihoku Shinkin Bank) announced on February 26 that they have decided to reduce their withdrawal limit by using cash cards to prevent damage to special scams.
For depositors aged 70 or older who have not made a certain amount of withdrawal transactions at ATMs for the past three years, the maximum amount that can be withdrawn by cash card is 500,000 yen.
On October 1, the Kuwana Mie Shinkin Bank and the Kita-Ise Ueno Shinkin Bank were lowered, and the Kihoku Shinkin Bank was lowered from November 1.
In the prefecture, there are many special fraud cases in which financial institutions, police officials, etc. fake cash cards and PIN numbers and are sent out at ATMs.
The sudden death of Chikakata ITSUTSU who was transferred to Mutsu room including Tsururyu YOKOTSUNA | Shizuoka Shimbun at Ess
The Japan Sumo Association announced on July 27 that it had approved the transfer of three sumo wrestlers from the Izutsu room including Tsururyu YOKOTSUNAMI and one Tokoyama to the Mutsu room following the death of Chikakata ITSUTSUKI.
The Mutsu room is the same as the Izutsu room.
His master, Chikakata MUTSU (former Kirishima Ozeki), was born in Izutsu's room and was a brother and son of Chikakata IZUTSU.
On the 16th, Chikakata ITSUTSU died suddenly, and Tsururyu and others were temporarily kept in the Kagamiyama room of the same family, and future treatment was discussed.
There are 12 sumo wrestlers in the Mutsu room, including Mt. Juryo Kirima from Mongolia, which is the same as Tsururyu.
