First Ice at Mt. Norikura Tatamidaira (Gifu Shimbun Web) - Yahoo!
Ice observed for the first time this season at Tsurugaike Pond in Mt. Norikura Tatamidaira = 27th morning, Tanseigawa-cho, Takayama City (provided by Norikura Skyline Management Office)
On the 27th, ice was observed for the first time this season at Tsurugaike Pond in Mt. Norikura, the Northern Alps.
Four days later than last year, one day earlier than the average of the past ten years.
According to Norikura Skyline Management Office, around 6:25 a.m., officials patrolling the road confirmed that there were about 2 mm thick ice on the west side of Tsuruke Pond.
The weather was fine and the temperature was 3 degrees.
According to the Gifu Regional Meteorological Observatory, the lowest temperature in the prefecture was 9-5 °C in Rokumaya, Sokawa-cho, the city.
