Publication of the original manuscript before the suicide of Akutagawa | Shizuoka Shimbun at Es
A manuscript written by Ryunosuke Akutagawa, which will be exhibited for the first time at the Tabata Bunshimura Memorial Hall
The author Ryunosuke AKUTAGAWA (1892-1927) obtained the manuscript of his essay "Shoku Bunshi-mura Memorial Hall" in Kita Ward, Tokyo by 27 days, which he published in his last years, in which he fought literary theory with Junichiro TANIZAKI.
It will be exhibited at the museum from October 1.
Although it was known that his essays were included in the whole collection, it was the first time that his manuscripts were published publicly.
It is thought that he wrote it a few months before Akutagawa committed suicide, and the museum researcher, Takeshi Tanei, said, "I can see how Akutagawa, who was mentally and mentally debilitated, faced serious literary challenges with a tragic resolution."
Twelve essays containing 200 characters were published in the April 27 issue of Bungei Shunju.
Greta Toonbeli: Why do adults laugh and threaten children?
Swedish environmental activist Greta Thunberg gave a speech at the United Nations Climate Action Summit in New York on September 23.
