How do I prevent dementia and keep it to the level of "forgetting things"?
Interviews and writings: Yo Watanabe
Major pharmaceutical companies and university hospitals have failed to challenge research and development.
However, the relationship between dementia and lifestyle habits has been elucidated, and it has become clear that there is a possibility that it can be extremely mild and forgotten.
Kinki University Hospital I talked to Professor Shunsuke Otsuki of the Stroke Center.
there's no dementia.
What is the current situation?
Otsuki: From mild to severe, everyone may become dementia when they age.
However, it is thought that it will still take more than 20 years to develop new dementia drugs.
Donepezil, a drug commonly used in Japan, has already been out of insurance coverage in some countries overseas, and we cannot expect a significant cure effect.
On the other hand, people can live longer, as deaths from infectious diseases and accidents have decreased, and cancer deaths have decreased due to remarkable advances in treatment of anticancer drugs.
Therefore, it is also true that dementia patients are increasing.
It is not something that can be solved by the individual or family alone, but it is necessary to create an environment in which society as a whole can live with peace of mind in the region.
How to keep things to the level of forgetting
― Are there people who are prone to dementia or who are difficult to become?
Otsuki: Even if it is inevitable to become dementia, it is possible to suppress symptoms as much as possible and stay at the level of "forgetting things."
Dementia is considered as one of lifestyle-related diseases, and tends to be easy to become.
First, people in Metabo tend to be prone to dementia.
Dementia is regarded as one of lifestyle-related diseases.
It is a combination of obesity, hypertension, diabetes and hypercholesterolemia.
It also affects the presence or absence of economic power.
For example, in the United States, food tickets are distributed to the poor, but food tickets are frozen hamburgers, pizzas and chickens that can be saved.
Gas and electricity cannot be used, and people living in an environment where they cannot cook can use it.
Then, it becomes a meal with fewer vegetables and proteins, and it becomes a life that is biased toward lipids and carbohydrates.
Eventually, poverty becomes obese, and when it comes to doing things, you only have to look at TV vaguely, and your body becomes disabled.
A similar situation could be Japan.
In addition, people who do not think about things and do not work tend to become dementia.
In other words, in order to prevent dementia, it is necessary to read books everyday and think about things that are not metabolized.
Okayama tourism and specialty PR in Osaka Bicchu Marche Manki-dong VR also appeared: Sanyo Newspaper Digital|San Digi
On the 27th, "Okayama Sunny Country Bicchu Marche" (hosted by the prefectural Bicchu Prefectural Bureau, etc.) was held in the plaza of JR Osaka Station.
At the beginning of this month, Niimi City, which was hit by local torrential rains, set up a VR (virtual reality) experience corner in Manki-do and sold its appeal to people in the Kansai area.
Seven towns of Kurashiki, Kasaoka, Ihara, Sosha, Niimi, Asaguchi and Yakake participated.
There were corners such as Uchiwa making using masking tape (Kurashiki City), denim key holder making (Ihara City), Mankakyo making (Asaguchi City) related to the telescope of the observatory, and station users stopped by.
During the VR experience in Manki-do, visitors used their own goggles to simulate walking in the cave.
A woman (52) from Itami City, Hyogo Prefecture said, "If you turn left and look right, you can see the scenery on the right, and I felt like I was really walking in.If you have the opportunity, I would like to experience the real Manki-do."
