Kansai Electric Power Co., Ltd. (Kansai Electric Power Co., Ltd.)
Kansai Electric Power Co., Ltd. chairman Makoto Yagi (69) and others received gold from Eiji Moriyama (who died at the age of 90 in March this year), a former assistant in Takahama-cho, Fukui Prefecture, where the Takahama nuclear power plant is located.
Construction company Yoshida Development was established in 1981.
According to the credit research company, net sales for the fiscal year ended August 2013 were 350 million yen, but exceeded 1 billion yen in the fiscal year ending August 15, and exceeded 2.1 billion yen in the fiscal year ending August 2006.
The construction of nuclear power plants at Sekiden accounted for much of the work.
"I'll kill you" - Yahoo!News
On the 24th of this month, a 33-year-old unemployed man was arrested on a national highway in Kagoshima City, suspected of driving a car relentlessly and threatening to kill a man who was driving.
The suspect, Miyahara Katsu (33), was arrested on suspicion of intimidation.
According to the police, suspect Miyahara has been suspected of intimidating a man by threatening to kill him at the intersection where he persistently drove a 24-year-old man on the national highway of Kagoshima City at 0 a.m. this month.
On the 25th, a man submitted a report of the damage and the police proceeded to investigate, but on the afternoon of the 26th, a suspect Miyahara went to the police station accompanied by a friend and was arrested.
Suspected Miyahara admitted the charge and said that he was forced to brake.
The police are investigating suspect Miyahara driving without a license.
