Okayama Art Exchange Opens in the City Center: Sanyo Shimbun Digital | San'Digi
People who go around the classroom in a video work depicting the future 3,000 years later
The international art exhibition "Okayama Art Exchange 2019" held every three years in central Okayama City (hosted by the executive committee of cities, prefectures, etc.) opened on the 27th.
Along with the mysterious title "IF THE SNAKE If Snake," 18 artists from 9 countries enjoy cutting-edge art.
This is the second time since 16 years, and we have invited the French artist Pierre Yuig as artistic director.
Approximately 40 films and three-dimensional works will be shown at 13 locations including former Uchiyama Shimoko (Marunouchi, Kita Ward, Okayama City) and the prefectural Tenjinyama Cultural Plaza (Marunouchi, Kita Ward, Okayama City).
Prior to the opening ceremony, a small opening ceremony was held, and about 100 people attended.
Mayor Masao Omori, General Producer Yasuharu Ishikawa, and other members of the executive committee, said, "It will be an exhibition that attracts attention from the world that stimulates intellectual sensibilities and stimulates imagination and creativity."
Families and children studying outside the school immediately visited the school and found a snake-shaped robot that responds to the surrounding sounds in the dohyo of the school yard, and walked around the school building, which turned into a stage for a video work depicting the world 3,000 years later.
I enjoyed the art that led to a different world.
While traveling with my father, a first-year high school student in Tokyo (15) said, "It's interesting to see the work that makes use of the atmosphere of the old school building, and I can imagine the time that flows into this place."
It is closed on Mondays (in case of national holidays) until November 24.
Hong Kong, rally in 5 years of the Umbrella Movement tens of thousands, aim for ordinary elections | Shizuoka Shimbun at Es
Five years have passed since the "Umbrella Movement" began, and people gathered at the meeting hall = 28th, Hong Kong (joint)
[Collaboration with Hong Kong] On the 28th of May, a large-scale demonstration called "Umbrella Movement" in 2014 called for democratization of Hong Kong's election, tens of thousands of people gathered in a park near the Hong Kong government headquarters building in Admiralty, where the largest demonstration base was located.
Some young people occupied the main road around the venue and threw a flame bottle at the government office.
As protests started with the amendment of the Fugitive Ordinance continued, the participants renewed their determination to fight until the realization of a "true ordinary election" that could not be won at the time.
In June, more than 79 days after the Umbrella Movement, 112 days of protests began, and the demands of the demonstrators expanded to "five major demands" such as electoral reform.
Ibaraki Kokutai Opening Day|Saga Newspaper News|Saga Newspaper
The 74th National Sports Festival "Ikiiki Ibaraki Yume National Sports Festival 2019" was held on October 28 at Kasamatsu Sports Park Athletic Stadium in Hitachinaka City, Ibaraki Prefecture.
About 400 players and directors from Saga Prefecture will participate in 33 competitions, excluding those held before the exhibition.
The prefecture ranked 43rd for three consecutive years until last year, but rose to 33rd last year.
We are also strengthening our efforts toward the national sports tournament held in the prefecture in 2023.
In the pre-event competition held by 16th, the Saga Girls' High School of rhythmic gymnastics and the adult girls and boys' girls of gymnastics all won 6th place and played.
I want to take advantage of the flow of each competition to advance to the top.
At the general opening ceremony, 83 athletes, directors, and executives from the prefectural government marched to the 40th place, and a rugby boy, Kugo Ishikawa (Saga Koka), was the flag bearer.
On the first day, wrestling, table tennis and karate are held.
